<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-01T11:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-01T11:24:00-05:00" n="868" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d868">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6040: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gade</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-01T18:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">January 1,
                                        1920—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 10:45
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>55. Military representatives of Esthonia inform armistice been arranged
                            between Esthonia and Bolsheviks to take effect January 3, 10:30 in the
                            morning.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_GJA1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Gade</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>